## Title
[Specific — 3 to 10 words. Do NOT use "Weekly 1:1" — name the actual topics.]

## Summary
3-5 sentences: what was discussed, key outcomes, concerns, tone.

## Detailed Notes
Narrative of the conversation in order — opening, what the employee raised, manager response, deeper dives, how it wrapped up. Capture tone shifts, hesitation, enthusiasm, moments of alignment or friction. Use direct quotes where the employee's exact words matter.

## Mood & Energy Check-in
Self-reported energy, work-life balance, stress indicators, enthusiasm. Tone — upbeat, flat, frustrated, energized?

## Accomplishments & Wins
Specific completed work, problems solved, positive feedback received, milestones reached, ownership shown.

## Progress Against Objectives
Goals/OKRs discussed, status, timeline changes, obstacles, any new objectives.

## Blockers & Challenges
For each: what is it, how is the employee handling it, what support do they need from the manager?

### Operational
Day-to-day system/access/tooling/on-call/incident-response issues.

### Organizational
Unclear ownership, cross-team dependencies, approval bottlenecks, staffing, meeting overload.

### Infrastructure / Physical
Hardware, network, equipment, office/remote setup.

### Roadmap / Strategic
Product direction, feature priorities, tech debt, migrations, vendor decisions.

## Feedback Given (Manager → Employee)
Use SBI where possible.
- **Positive:** situation / behavior / impact
- **Constructive:** examples, agreed approach

## Feedback Received (Employee → Manager / Org)
Upward feedback — about manager style, team processes, leadership, tools, culture. Often subtle; capture it even when expressed as complaints or suggestions.

{{ m.vendor_feedback_block(vendors) }}

## Customer & Stakeholder Feedback
What the employee shared about customer interactions, stakeholder relationships, external feedback.

## Team & Organization Observations
Team dynamics, morale, process friction, culture, recent org changes, strategy clarity.

## Career Development & Growth
Short-term learning goals, long-term aspirations, stretch assignments, training, mentoring, promotion readiness.

## Coaching Notes
Coaching topic / options explored / agreed next step / commitments.

## Engagement & Wellbeing Signals
Factual observations, not judgments.

### Positive
Volunteering ideas, enthusiasm, discussing future plans here, initiative, mentoring, asking about growth.

### Concerning
Short answers, low energy, cynicism, dissatisfaction with role/comp/growth, burnout or overwhelm, checking out.

